  "prompt": "How much salary in Indian rupees is considered good in japan?",
  "response": "The concept of a \"good salary\" in Japan can vary widely depending on factors such as the cost of living in different regions, the industry, and individual lifestyle. However, to provide some context:\n\n1. **Average Salary**: As of recent data, the average annual salary in Japan is around \u00a54 million to \u00a56 million (approximately \u20b925 lakhs to \u20b937 lakhs) per year.\n\n2. **Cost of Living**: Major cities like Tokyo and Osaka have higher costs of living compared to rural areas. In Tokyo, a monthly salary of around \u00a5300,000 to \u00a5400,000 (approximately \u20b91.87 lakhs to \u20b92.49 lakhs) is often considered decent.\n\n3. **Foreign Workers**: For expatriates or foreign workers, salaries can vary greatly depending on qualifications and job roles. Many foreign professionals may earn a monthly salary in the range of \u00a5500,000 to \u00a51,000,000 (approximately \u20b93.11 lakhs to \u20b96.22 lakhs), which would be considered good.\n\n4. **Quality of Life**: A salary that allows for comfortable living, savings, and leisure activities is generally considered good. In urban areas, this might require higher earnings due to housing and transportation costs.\n\nIn summary, while a salary of around \u00a54 million per year (\u20b925 lakhs) can be considered decent, individual circumstances and locations will influence what is considered a good salary.",
